      "author": "gabbywelson",
      "description": "First public release of Corduroy.\n\nSearch Google Maps from the command palette and insert a place's coordinates (and optionally its formatted address) into the active note's frontmatter — ready for map plugins like Obsidian Leaflet and Map View.\n\n**Install manually:** download `main.js`, `manifest.json`, and `styles.css` into `<vault>/.obsidian/plugins/corduroy/`, then enable Corduroy in Settings → Community plugins.\n\nRequires a Google Places API (New) key (configured in the plugin settings; stored in Obsidian's secret storage). Requires Obsidian 1.11.4+.",
